name: Earliest Occurring Unique Value  in Stream
description:
Given a stream of values, return the earliest occurring unique value up to that point.
If there are no unique values, return nil.

For example,
```ruby
input(5) #=> 5
input(3) #=> 5
input(2) #=> 5
input(1) #=> 5
input(5) #=> 3
input(3) #=> 2
input(1) #=> 2
input(0) #=> 2
input(2) #=> 0
```

Your function should be handle objects of any type, not just ints.
Test cases include floats and strings!
Note: the input may be extremely long, so be mindful of speed!
